  output: # Formatting Whole-Number Averages Without Trailing Decimals

When writing an average to the spreadsheet, check if the result is mathematically a whole number. If so, output as integer—omit any extraneous ".0".

```python
# Detect and suppress trailing zeros for whole averages
value = total / count
if value == int(value):
    formatted = str(int(value))  # "50"
else:
    formatted = "{:.2f}".format(value)  # "50.25"
ws["E10"] = formatted
```

